			title: "YUNG's Handiwork"
			icon: "travelerscompass:travelers_compass"
			description: [
				"§6YUNG's mods replace nearly every vanilla structure with a handcrafted§r"
				"§6redesign — more rooms, better loot, actual architecture.§r"
				""
				"§eAll YUNG's structures in the pack:§r"
				"§7• §eBetter Dungeons§7 — each dungeon type has 4+ layout variants."
				"§7• §eBetter Strongholds§7 — multi-wing maze with real boss rooms."
				"§7• §eBetter Mineshafts§7 — branching tunnels with cave-in setpieces."
				"§7• §eBetter Desert Temples§7 — actual traps that can kill you."
				"§7• §eBetter Jungle Temples§7 — redesigned with lore rooms."
				"§7• §eBetter Witch Huts§7 — expanded with crafting rooms and ingredient storage."
				"§7• §eBetter Nether Fortresses§7 — wider corridors, better spawner placement."
				"§7• §eBetter Ocean Monuments§7 — cleaner Guardian arenas."
				"§7• §eBetter End Island§7 — the outer End islands are restructured."
				"§7• §eCave Biomes§7 — full cave biomes underground (lush, dripstone overhaul)."
				"§7• §eBridges§7 — procedural bridges across ravines and rivers."
				"§7• §eExtras§7 — wells, ruins, small camps across all biomes."
				""
				"§7Use §eExplorer's Compass§7 (quest reward above) to target a specific type."
				""
				"§a► Clear any YUNG's redesigned structure. Mark done."
			]
			dependencies: ["00120001"]
		}

