			icon: "minecraft:beehive"
			description: [
				"§6The Bumblezone is a bee-themed dimension — a vast honeycomb§r"
				"§6world filled with bee structures, honey lakes, pollen fields,§r"
				"§6and unique bee-based mobs not found anywhere else.§r"
				""
				"§eHow to enter The Bumblezone:§r"
				"§7• §eBuild§7 a 3×3 §eHoneycomb Block§7 frame (no corners needed)."
				"§7• §ePlace§7ony Honey Block in the center."
				"§7• §eRight-click§7 the Honey Block with a §eBee§7 in your hand."
				"§7• The portal activates — step through."
				""
				"§eAlternative entry:§r"
				"§7• A naturally-occurring portal can sometimes be found inside§7"
				"§7  §elarge bee nests§7 in Terralith biomes. Rare but real."
				""
				"§eWhat you'll find:§r"
				"§7• §eHoneycomb terrain§7 — navigable tunnels of massive wax honeycomb."
				"§7• §eBumble Bee mobs§7 — passive giant bees that aggro if attacked."
				"§7• §ePollen fields§7 — unique blocks with crafting uses."
				"§7• §eBumblezone Honey§7 — better healing than vanilla honey bottles."
				"§7• §eHive Castles§7 — structured dungeons guarded by elite bee mobs."
				""
				"§a► Enter The Bumblezone and collect any Bumblezone Honeycomb. Mark done."
